Line the ammo canister with a garbage bag and pack the plates and hardware inside.  Again, be as careful as practical to reduce the chances for leaks.  All 16 plates and 4 bags of hardware should fit into the one ammo canister.  Depending on how much space is left, you may need to add styrofoam peanuts or other packing material. It would be good if you could gently rotate the canister onto each side every day or two until shipment to insure that all surfaces stay wetted with formalin.  The canister should be shipped to the Havana Field Station.  Because of the formaldehyde, I suggest/request you ship it UPS.  \par 
\par 
We would also like for you to ship the 125 ml bottles containing the preserved microscope slides to the same address.  Again, shipping UPS is preferred.  \par 
Finally, I would like photocopies of your zebra mussel monitoring data sheets.\par 
\par 
The plastic container is yours to keep (big deal huh!).\par 
\par 
Again, your cooperation and assistance are greatly appreciated.\par 
